{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/dvt-prevention-for-travellers/background-information/risk-factors-for-travel-related-dvt/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"e1dae635-f691-5ca9-85dc-e8547330d64d","slug":"risk-factors-for-travel-related-dvt","fullItemName":"Risk factors for travel-related DVT","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field d89b230c-7948-4fd6-b540-e581fb5428cd --><h2>What are the risk factors for travel-related deep vein thrombosis?</h2><!-- end field d89b230c-7948-4fd6-b540-e581fb5428cd -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 4e1915af-a96b-4db1-b2cc-32cbb71666b0 --><!-- begin field eecc0d1a-f944-4270-be5d-4e5b785aa53f --><ul><li>The relative risk of travel-related deep vein thrombosis (DVT) is further increased if other risk factors for developing DVT are present. These include:<ul><li>Active malignancy. </li><li>A family history of DVT or pulmonary embolism (PE) in a close family member.</li><li>Aged over 60 years. </li><li>Extremes of height — people taller than 1.90 metres or shorter than 1.60 metres.<ul><li>Shorter people may experience seat edge pressure to the popliteal area. </li><li>Taller people have less leg room.</li></ul></li><li>Inherited blood-clotting abnormalities.</li><li>Large varicose veins or chronic venous insufficiency. </li><li>Limited mobility (for example, a lower-limb fracture in plaster). </li><li>Obesity (body mass index greater than 30 kg/m<sup>2</sup>). </li><li>Polycythaemia. </li><li>Pregnancy, or up to six weeks postpartum. </li><li>Previous DVT or PE. </li><li>Recent surgery or trauma, particularly to the abdomen, pelvic region, or legs. </li><li>Thrombophilia (such as factor V Leiden mutation or antiphospholipid syndrome), or other thrombotic states (for example, heart failure, recent myocardial infarction, severe infection, inflammatory bowel disease). </li><li>Use of oestrogens, such as oral contraceptives or hormone replacement therapy.<ul></ul></li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/dvt-prevention-for-travellers/references/\">Watson and Baglin, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/dvt-prevention-for-travellers/references/\">WHO, 2012</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/dvt-prevention-for-travellers/references/\">SIGN, 2014</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/dvt-prevention-for-travellers/references/\">CDC, 2017</a>]</p><!-- end field eecc0d1a-f944-4270-be5d-4e5b785aa53f --><!-- end item 4e1915af-a96b-4db1-b2cc-32cbb71666b0 -->","topic":{"id":"cae1071e-3c91-5b56-b502-a61f0f71ef81","topicId":"3c669132-4496-4b66-90fd-d2b56b8a4bd9","topicName":"DVT prevention for travellers","slug":"dvt-prevention-for-travellers","lastRevised":"Last revised in August 2018","chapters":[{"id":"3f8095c9-6fe5-5e49-b39a-e540920dda99","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"25a24ce8-f321-5b79-8d73-8addddb2f502","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9da34e7b-6a4a-579a-8b21-0afc95a9205a","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"3af2d84d-93af-5838-9695-9b777b6dc0cf","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2b494570-aa55-5b36-bd1f-30bc9a6098b4","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"43385fe8-2538-58b1-a59b-43a3132f0df4","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"7415be35-e01a-5aec-a818-757b23c4a254","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"81a1aa0c-0499-52ea-9a5a-c4888dcbfdf9","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"99876960-e358-5e14-8138-79a85d5d012f","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"3a1bd3b0-862c-55dc-9dca-1cd5b2c6354f","slug":"qof-indicators","fullI